sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Edge as Edge Node
    participant UNS as MQTT Broker
    participant Bridge as ERP–UNS Bridge
    participant API as BC API Layer
    participant Exec as Operation Execution

    note over Edge,Exec: Scenario: Messages Arrive Out of Order

    Edge->>UNS: PUBLISH (T1)<br/>qtyProduced: 100
    Edge->>UNS: PUBLISH (T2)<br/>qtyProduced: 200
    Edge->>UNS: PUBLISH (T3)<br/>qtyProduced: 300

    note over UNS,Bridge: Network delivers T3 first, then T1

    UNS-->>Bridge: DELIVER T3<br/>qtyProduced: 300, sourceTimestamp: "T3"

    Bridge->>API: POST /executionEvents<br/>{ qtyProduced: 300, sourceTimestamp: "T3" }
    API->>Exec: UPSERT<br/>qtyProduced = 300, sourceTimestamp = T3
    API-->>Bridge: 200 OK

    UNS-->>Bridge: DELIVER T1 (delayed)<br/>qtyProduced: 100, sourceTimestamp: "T1"

    Bridge->>API: POST /executionEvents<br/>{ qtyProduced: 100, sourceTimestamp: "T1" }

    API->>Exec: Check sourceTimestamp
    Exec-->>API: Current: T3

    note over API: T1 < T3 – reject stale update

    API->>Inbox: INSERT record<br/>Status = "Skipped"<br/>Note = "Stale timestamp"

    API-->>Bridge: 200 OK<br/>{ processed: false,<br/>reason: "Stale: newer data exists" }

    note over Edge,Exec: Result: Latest data (T3) preserved

